# Modern CLI Tool Tips
# Format: modern_tool|old_command_pattern|description|example
#
# These tips teach you to use modern Rust-based CLI tools directly.
# The old commands still work - these are better alternatives!

bat|cat |Syntax-highlighted file viewing with line numbers|bat ~/.zshrc
fd|find |Faster, friendlier file finding with smart defaults|fd "*.md" ~/Documents
rg|grep |Blazing fast recursive search with context|rg "TODO" --type=go
dust|du |Visual disk usage with intuitive bar charts|dust ~/Downloads
procs|ps |Modern process viewer with tree and search|procs --tree
btm|top |Beautiful system monitor with graphs|btm
z|cd |Smart directory jumping - learns your habits|z projects
ll|ls -la|List files with git status, icons, and grouping|ll ~/Documents
la|ls -a|List all files including hidden|la
tree|tree |Tree view with git awareness and icons|tree ~/dotfiles
